definition.value: The monocarboxylic acid amide resulting from the formal condensation of the aryl amino group of N-(4-fluorophenyl)-1-(2-phenylethyl)piperidin-4-amine with propanoic acid.
A branched mannopentaose consisting of five D-mannosyl residues linked via alpha(1->3) and alpha(1->6) glycosidic bonds.
A hydroxamic acid-type histone deacetylase (HDAC) inhibitor with antineoplastic activity.
A dicarboxylic acid diamide comprising suberic (octanedioic) acid coupled to aniline and 1,2-diaminobenzene.
A nucleoside bisphosphate that has a purine nucleobase.
A nucleoside bisphosphate where sugar of the nucleoside is ribose.

A cyclodepsipeptide consisting of the cyclic disulfide of (2Z)-2-aminobut-2-enoyl, L-valyl, (3S,4E)-3-hydroxy-7-sulfanylhept-4-enoyl, D-valyl and D-cysteinyl residues coupled in sequence and cyclised head-to tail.
A nucleotide in which two nucleosides are joined together through their 5' carbons by a chain of phosphate molecules.
A peptidoglycan with a phosphate linkage to a lipid.
A monocarboxylic acid amide resulting from the formal condensation of the aryl amino group of methyl 4-anilino-1-(2-phenylethyl)piperidine-4-carboxylate with propanoic acid.
An alpha-amino-acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-sulfino-L-alanine, arising from deprotonation of the sulfino and carboxy groups and protonation of the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A glycoside consisting of D-ribitol having a alpha-D-glucosyl-(1->3)-alpha-D-glucosyl-(1->3)-alpha-L-rhamnosyl moiety attached at the 3-position.
A heptasaccharide derivative corresponding to the core oligosaccharide of the L1 immunotype of Neisseria meningitidis.
A dipeptide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxylic acid group of S-nitroso-L-cysteine with the amino group of glycine.
A resorcinol having methyl and pentyl groups at positions 4 and 5 respectively.
A alpha-L-rhamnoside consisting of D-ribitol having an alpha-L-rhamnosyl residue attached at the 3-position.
A glycoside comprising glucose in (1->3) linkage with rhamnose, in turn linked (1->3) to D-ribitol.
The monocarboxylic acid amide resulting from the formal condensation of the aryl amino group of 3-methyl-N-phenyl-1-(2-phenylethyl)piperidin-4-amine with propanoic acid.

A sialooctaosylceramide consisting of a branched nonasaccharide made up from one sialyl residue, three galactose residues, two L-fucose residues, two N-acetylglucosamine residues and one glucose residue, which at the reducing end is attached to the ceramide portion via a beta-linkage.
A glycoside formed by successive (1->3) linkage of galactose, glucose, rhamnose and ribitol moieties.
The carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the aryl amino group of methyl 4-anilino-3-methyl-1-(2-phenylethyl)piperidine-4-carboxylate with propanoic acid.
A ganglioside in which the oligosaccharide portion is composed of an octasaccharide, to which one or more sialic acid residues are attached.
An alpha-L-rhamnoside consisting of D-ribitol having an alpha-L-rhamnosyl residue attached at the 4-position.
An organic anion which is obtained by removal of a proton from the hydroxy group of sorgoleone. The major form of sorgoleone at pH 7.3.
An anilide resulting from the formal condensation of the aryl amino group of N-phenyl-1-[2-(2-thienyl)ethyl]piperidin-4-amine with propanoic acid.
A glycoside comprising glucose in (1->3) linkage with rhamnose, in turn linked (1->4) to D-ribitol.
A glycoside formed by successive (1->3) linkage of galactose, glucose and rhamnose, which is then linked (1->4) to D-ribitol.
The monocarboxylic acid amide resulting from the formal condensation of the aryl amino group of 1-methyl-N-phenylpiperidin-4-amine with propanoic acid.
A tetrasaccharide derivative comprising alpha-D-Galp-(1->3)-alpha-D-Glcp-(1->3)-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-D-ribitol phosphorylated at position 5 of ribitol.
The dicarboxylic acid monoamide resulting from the formal condensation of aryl amino group of N-phenyl-1-(2-phenylethyl)piperidin-4-amine with succinic acid.
A tetrasaccharide derivative comprising alpha-D-Galp-(1->3)-alpha-D-Glcp-(1->3)-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->4)-D-ribitol phosphorylated at position 5 of ribitol.
A tetrasaccharide derivative comprising the alpha-D-Glcp-(1->3)-alpha-D-Glcp-(1->3)-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-D-ribitol phosphorylated at position 5 of ribitol.
A nucleotide-sugar whose nucleobase is a pyrimidine.
A laminarabiose having beta-configuration at the reducing end anomeric centre.
An organic phosphonate of formula (RO)2P(=O)-CR2-NR2; R can be H.
A member of the class of thiocyanates that is the methyl ester of thiocyanic acid.
An organoammonium salt where dicyclohexylammonium is the cation and  alpha,N-(epsilon,N-DNP-aminocaproyl)-epsilon,N-DNP-L-lysinate is the counterion.
A dipeptide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxylic acid group of 4-aminobenzoic acid with the amino group of L-glutamic acid.
An EC 3.5.1.* (non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase) inhibitor that interferes with the function of histone deacetylase (EC 3.5.1.98).
An organochlorine compound comprising trans-cinnamic acid having a chloro substituent at the 4-position on the phenyl ring.
A member of the family of benzoquinones, sorgoleone is 2-hydroxy-5-methoxy-1,4-benzoquinone in which the hydrogen at position 3 is substituted by a (4Z,7Z)-pentadeca-1,4,7-trien-15-yl group.
A cinnamic acid having a methyl substituent at the 3-position on the phenyl ring.
A dTDP-sugar having either D- or L-rhamnose as the sugar component.
Any compound that has a nucleobase as a part.
Any member of the group of bioactive lipids made by oxidation of polyunsaturated fatty acids.
